/* loops.cdo -- pure loop-overhead micro-benchmark.
 *
 * Stresses: backedge dispatch, local variable load/store, integer
 * arithmetic.  Useful as a sanity check that the JIT is recording the
 * smallest possible loop -- if this doesn't speed up, something is
 * wrong with hot-path detection.
 *
 * NOTE: today's interpreter materialises FOR-IN ranges on the value
 * stack (2048 slots), so the inner range is kept short and total
 * iteration count is driven by the outer loop.  Once a fix lands for
 * that, this benchmark can be a single 1M-iteration loop.
 */

VAR sum = 0;
FOR outer IN 1 -> 1000 {
    FOR i IN 1 -> 1000 {
        sum = sum + i;
    }
}
print(sum);
